  <void property="longDescription"> 
   <string>
By means of read magic, you can read magical inscriptions on
objects---books, scrolls, weapons, and the like---that
would otherwise be unintelligible. This deciphering does not
normally invoke the magic contained in the writing, although it
may do so in the case of a cursed scroll. Furthermore, once the
spell is cast and you have read the magical inscription, you are
thereafter able to read that particular writing without recourse
to the use of read magic. You can read at the rate of one page
(250 words) per minute. The spell allows you to identify a glyph
of warding with a successful Spellcraft check against DC 13 or a
symbol with a successful Spellcraft check against DC 19.
